# HorizCoin Node Operator Guide

## Prerequisites
- Cloud server (AWS, GCP, Azure, Hetzner, OVH, etc.)
- Docker or Rust toolchain installed
- Reliable high-speed Ethernet connection (minimum 100Mbps up/down)

## Setup Steps

1. **Clone the repository**
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/thehorizonholding/HorizCoin.git
   cd HorizCoin
   ```

2. **Edit `config.yaml`**
   - Set your node ID, keys, bandwidth target, and peers.

3. **Build and run the node**
   - **Rust:**  
     ```bash
     cargo build --release
     ./target/release/node
     ```
   - **Docker:**  
     ```bash
     docker build -t horizcoin-node .
     docker run -p 30303:30303 -v $(pwd)/config.yaml:/app/config.yaml horizcoin-node
     ```

4. **Connect to bootstrap peers**
   - Ensure your config lists at least one active peer.

5. **Monitor logs**
   - Logs will display bandwidth proofs and peer connections.
   - For troubleshooting, check `/var/log/horizcoin-node.log` (if configured).

## Security & Compliance

- Ensure your firewall allows TCP port 30303
- Use secure key handling (never share your private key)
- Enable TLS for encrypted node-to-node communication (future release)

## Support

- For help, open an [issue on GitHub](https://github.com/thehorizonholding/HorizCoin/issues)
- Join Discord or community forums for operator discussions
